  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joshua Addresses the Israelites'
      title: Joshua Addresses the Israelites
      number: 1
      content: 'After the death of Moses the servant of Yahweh, Yahweh said to Joshua
        son of Nun, the assistant of Moses, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CMy servant Moses is dead. Get up and cross the Jordan, you
        and all this people, into the land that I am giving to them, to the Israelites.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Every place that the soles of your feet will tread, I have given
        it to you, as I promised to Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'From the wilderness and the Lebanon, up to the great river, the river
        Euphrates, all of the land of the Hittites, and up to the great sea in the
        west, will be your territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'No one will stand before you all the days of your life. Just as I
        was with Moses, so will I be with you; I will not fail you, and I will not
        forsake you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Be strong and courageous, for you will give the people this land
        as an inheritance that I swore to their ancestors to give them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Only be strong and very courageous to observe diligently the whole
        law that Moses my servant commanded you. Do not turn aside from it, to the
        right or left, so that you may succeed wherever you go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The scroll of this law will not depart from your mouth; you will
        meditate on it day and night so that you may observe diligently all that
        is written in it. For then you will succeed in your ways and prosper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Did I not command you? Be strong and courageous! Do not fear or be
        dismayed, for Yahweh your God is with you wherever you go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Joshua commanded the officers of the people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CPass through the midst of the camp and command the people:
        \u2018Prepare your provisions; in three days you are to cross the Jordan
        to go possess the land that Yahweh your God is giving you to possess.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'To the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh Joshua
        said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CRemember the word that Moses Yahweh\u2019s servant commanded
        you, saying, \u2018Yahweh your God is giving rest to you, and he is giving
        you this land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Your wives, your little children, and your livestock, they will remain
        in the land that Moses gave to you beyond the Jordan. All of the best fighting
        men will cross armed in front of your families; they will help you '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "until Yahweh gives rest to your families as well as to you. They
        will take possession of the land that Yahweh your God is giving to them.
        Then you will return to your own land and take possession of it, the land
        that Moses the servant of Yahweh gave you beyond the Jordan to the east.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And they answered Joshua, saying, \u201CAll that you have commanded
        us we will do, and wherever you will send us we will go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Just as we obeyed Moses, so will we obey you. Only may Yahweh your
        God be with you, as he was with Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Whoever rebels against your orders and does not obey your words according
        to what you commanded us will be put to death. Only be strong and courageous.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Spies View the Land'
      title: Spies View the Land
      number: 1
      content: "Then Joshua son of Nun secretly sent two men from Acacia Grove as
        spies, saying, \u201CGo, view the land, especially Jericho.\u201D So they
        went, and entered the house of a prostitute whose name was Rahab, and spent
        the night there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The king of Jericho was told, \u201CLook, some men from the Israelites
        have come here tonight to search out the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the king of Jericho sent for Rahab, saying, \u201CBring out the
        men who came to you, the ones who have entered your house, for they have
        come to search out the whole land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the woman took the two men and hid them. And she said, \u201CYes,
        the men came to me, but I did not know where they were from. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And when it was time to shut the gate for the night, the men left,
        and I do not know where they went. Chase after them quickly, for you may
        catch up to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(But she had taken them to the roof and had hidden them in the stalks
        of flax that she had spread out on the roof.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So the men chased after them on the way to the Jordan at the fords;
        and they shut the gate behind the pursuers that had gone out after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Before they went to sleep, she came up to them on the roof '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and said to the men, \u201CI know that Yahweh has given you the land,
        and that dread of you has fallen on us, and that all the inhabitants of the
        land melt away in fear because of your presence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For we have heard how Yahweh dried up the waters of the Red Sea before
        you when you went out from Egypt, and what you did to the two kings of the
        Amorites that were beyond the Jordan, Sihon and Og, whom you utterly destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'We heard this, and our hearts melted, and no courage was left in
        anyone because of your presence. For Yahweh your God is God in the heavens
        above and on the earth below. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So then please swear to me by Yahweh, because I have shown loyalty
        to you, and you will also show loyalty to my family. You must give me a sign
        of good faith,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and you will spare my father and mother, my brothers and sisters,
        and all that belongs to them; you will deliver our lives from death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the men said to her, \u201COur lives for yours. If you do not
        report this business of ours, we will show you loyalty and faithfulness when
        Yahweh gives us the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then she lowered them with a rope through the window, as her house
        was on the outer side of the wall, and she was residing in the wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And she said to them, \u201CGo to the mountain, so that the pursuers
        will not find you, and hide yourselves there three days until the pursuers
        return, and afterward you may go on your way.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The men said to her, \u201CWe will be released from this oath of
        yours that you made us swear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When we come to the land, you must tie this scarlet cord in the window
        through which you let us down, and you must gather your father and mother,
        and your brothers, and your whole family to your house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If anyone goes outside the doors of your house, they will be responsible
        for their own death, and we will be innocent. Anyone who will be with you
        in the house, we will be responsible for their death if a hand is laid on
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But if you report this business of ours, we will be released from
        your oath that you made us swear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And she said, \u201CAccording to your word it will be.\u201D Then
        she sent them away, and they went, and she tied the scarlet cord in the window. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They departed and came to the mountain, and they stayed there three
        days until the pursuers returned. The pursuers searched all along the way
        but did not find them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The two men returned and went down from the mountain, and they crossed
        over and came to Joshua son of Nun, and they told him everything that happened
        to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "They said to Joshua, \u201CSurely Yahweh has given all the land into
        our hand; also, all the inhabitants of the land melt away in fear because
        of our presence.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Israelites Cross the Jordan'
      title: The Israelites Cross the Jordan
      number: 1
      content: 'Joshua rose early in the morning, and they set out from Acacia Grove.
        And they came up to the Jordan, he and all the Israelites, and they spent
        the night there before they crossed over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'At the end of the three days the officers passed through the midst
        of the camp, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and they commanded the people: \u201CWhen you see the Levitical priests
        carrying the ark of the covenant of Yahweh your God you must set out from
        your place and go after it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But there will be a distance between you and it of about two thousand
        cubits in measurement. Do not come near it, so that you may know the way
        that you must go, for you have not passed on this way before.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Joshua said to the people, \u201CSanctify yourselves, because
        tomorrow Yahweh will do wonders in your midst.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Joshua said to the priests, \u201CTake up the ark of the covenant
        and cross over ahead of the people.\u201D And they took up the ark of the
        covenant and went ahead of the people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Yahweh said to Joshua, \u201CThis day I will begin exalting
        you in the sight of all Israel, that they may know that I was with Moses,
        and I will be with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You will command the priests carrying the ark of the covenant, saying,
        \u2018At the moment that you come to the edge of the waters of the Jordan,
        you will stand still in the Jordan.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Joshua said to the Israelites, \u201CCome here, and hear the
        words of Yahweh your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Joshua said, \u201CBy this you will know that the living God is in
        your midst, and he will certainly drive out the Canaanites from before you,
        and the Hittites, Hivites, the Perizzites, the Girgashites, the Amorites,
        and the Jebusites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Look! The ark of the covenant of the Lord of all the earth is about
        to cross over ahead of you into the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So then, take twelve men from the tribes of Israel, one from each
        tribe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When the soles of the feet of the priests carrying the ark of Yahweh,
        Lord of all the earth, rest in the waters of the Jordan, the waters of the
        Jordan will be cut off upstream, and they will stand still in one heap. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And it happened, when the people set out from their tents to cross
        over the Jordan, the priests carrying the ark of the covenant were ahead
        of the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When those carrying the ark came up to the Jordan, and the priests
        carrying the ark dipped their feet in the edge of the water (the Jordan was
        flowing over its banks during all the days of harvest), '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the waters flowing down from above stood still; they stood up in
        one heap very far from Adam, the city that is beside Zarethan, while the
        waters flowing down to the sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea, were completely
        cut off; and the people crossed over opposite Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the priests carrying the ark of the covenant of Yahweh stood
        firmly on the dry land in the middle of the Jordan while all Israel crossed
        on dry ground, until all the nation finished crossing the Jordan. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Israelites Make a Memorial'
      title: The Israelites Make a Memorial
      number: 1
      content: 'After all the nation finished crossing the Jordan, Yahweh said to
        Joshua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTake twelve men from the people, one man from each tribe,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and command them, saying, \u2018Take for yourselves twelve stones
        from the middle of the Jordan where the priests\u2019 feet stood firmly,
        and bring them over with you, and set them up in the place where you will
        camp tonight.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Joshua summoned the twelve men whom he had appointed from the
        Israelites, one from each tribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Joshua said to them, \u201CCross over before the ark of Yahweh
        your God to the middle of the Jordan, and each one of you lift up a stone
        on your shoulder, according to the number of the tribes of the Israelites,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "so that this may be a reminder among you. When your children ask
        in the future, saying, \u2018What do these stones mean to you?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "you will say to them that the waters of the Jordan were cut off from
        before the ark of the covenant of Yahweh. When it crossed the Jordan, the
        waters of the Jordan were cut off. These stones will be as a memorial for
        the Israelites for eternity.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Thus the Israelites did as Joshua commanded. They took twelve stones
        from the middle of the Jordan as Yahweh told Joshua, according to the number
        of the tribes of the Israelites, and they carried them over with them to
        the camp, and they put them there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Joshua set up twelve stones in the middle of the Jordan, in
        the place where the feet of the priests carrying the ark of the covenant
        stood, and they are there to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The priests carrying the ark remained standing in the middle of the
        Jordan until everything that Yahweh commanded Joshua to tell the people was
        finished, according to all that Moses commanded Joshua. And the people hastily
        crossed over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it happened, when all the people had finished crossing, the ark
        of Yahweh and the priests crossed over in front of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The children of Reuben, Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh crossed
        over armed before the Israelites, as Moses told them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'About forty thousand armed for fighting crossed over before the presence
        of Yahweh to the plains of Jericho for battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'On that day Yahweh exalted Joshua in the sight of all Israel, and
        they respected him as they respected Moses all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Yahweh said to Joshua, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CCommand the priests carrying the ark of the testimony to come
        up from the Jordan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Joshua commanded the priests, saying, \u201CCome up from the Jordan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And it happened that when the priests carrying the ark came up from
        the middle of the Jordan, and the soles of the priests\u2019 feet touched
        dry land, the waters of the Jordan returned to their place and flowed over
        all its banks as before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the people came up from the Jordan on the tenth day of the first
        month, and they camped in Gilgal on the eastern edge of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And those twelve stones that they took from the Jordan, Joshua set
        up in Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he said to the Israelites, \u201CWhen your children ask in the
        future their parents, \u2018What is the meaning of these stones?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "you will let your children know by saying, \u2018Israel crossed this
        Jordan on dry ground.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For Yahweh your God dried up the waters of the Jordan before you,
        until you had crossed, just as Yahweh your God did to the Red Sea, which
        he dried up before us until we had crossed over, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "so that all the peoples of the earth may know that the hand of Yahweh
        is strong, so that you may fear Yahweh your God forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Israelites Are Circumcised'
      title: The Israelites Are Circumcised
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened, when all the kings of the Amorites who were beyond
        the Jordan to the west, and all the kings of the Canaanites who were by the
        sea heard that Yahweh dried up the waters of the Jordan in front of the Israelites
        until they crossed over, their hearts melted, and there was no courage left
        in them because of the presence of the Israelites.   '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "At that time Yahweh said to Joshua, \u201CMake for yourself knives
        of flint, and circumcise the Israelites a second time.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Joshua made knives of flint, and he circumcised the Israelites
        at the hill of the foreskins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'This is the reason why Joshua circumcised all the people: all the
        males who went out from Egypt, all the warriors, died in the wilderness as
        they went out from Egypt on the journey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For all the people who left were circumcised, but all the people
        born in the wilderness on the journey after they left from Egypt were not
        circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For forty years the Israelites traveled in the wilderness until all
        the nation, the warriors that left Egypt, perished, because they did not
        listen to the voice of Yahweh. To them Yahweh swore that they would not see
        the land that he swore to their ancestors to give to us, a land flowing with
        milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Israelites Celebrate Passover in Canaan'
      title: The Israelites Celebrate Passover in Canaan
      number: 7
      content: 'And it was their children whom he raised in their place that Joshua
        circumcised, for they were uncircumcised, because they had not been circumcised
        on the journey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And it happened, when all the nation had finished circumcising, they
        remained where they were in the camp until they recovered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Yahweh said to Joshua, \u201CToday I have rolled away the disgrace
        of Egypt from you.\u201D Therefore, the name of that place is called Gilgal
        to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the Israelites camped at Gilgal, and they kept the Passover on
        the fourteenth day of the month, in the evening, on the plains of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'On the next day after the Passover, on that very day, they ate from
        the produce of the land, unleavened cakes and roasted corn. '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: The Commander of Yahweh\u2019s Army Appears Before Joshua"
      title: "The Commander of Yahweh\u2019s Army Appears Before Joshua"
      number: 12
      content: 'And the manna ceased the day after, when they started eating the
        produce of the land, and there was no longer manna for the Israelites. They
        ate from the crop of the land of Canaan in that year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And it happened, when Joshua was by Jericho, he looked up, and he
        saw a man standing opposite him with his sword drawn in his hand. And Joshua
        went to him and said, \u201CAre you with us, or with our adversaries?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he said, \u201CNeither. I have come now as the commander of Yahweh\u2019s
        army.\u201D And Joshua fell on his face to the earth, and he bowed down and
        said to him, \u201CWhat is my lord commanding his servant?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The commander of Yahweh\u2019s army said to Joshua, \u201CTake off
        your sandals from your feet, for the place where you are standing is holy.\u201D
        And Joshua did so. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Battle of Jericho'
      title: The Battle of Jericho
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Jericho was shut up inside and out because of the presence of
        the Israelites; no one was going out or coming in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Yahweh said to Joshua, \u201CLook, I am giving Jericho into your
        hand, its king and the soldiers of the army. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You will march around the city, all the warriors circling the city
        once; you will do so for six days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And seven priests will bear seven trumpets of rams\u2019 horns before
        the ark. On the seventh day you will march around the city seven times, and
        the priests will blow on the trumpets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And when they blow long on the horn of the ram, when you hear the
        sound of the trumpet, all the people will shout with a great war cry, and
        the wall of the city will fall flat, and the people will charge, each one
        straight ahead.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Joshua son of Nun summoned the priests and said to them, \u201CTake
        up the ark of the covenant, and let seven priests carry the trumpets of the
        rams\u2019 horns before the ark of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he said to the people, \u201CGo forward and march around the
        city, and let the armed men pass before the ark of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And when Joshua spoke to the people, the seven priests carrying the
        seven trumpets of rams\u2019 horns before the presence of Yahweh went forward
        and they blew the trumpets; and the ark of the covenant of Yahweh followed
        behind them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the armed men went before the priests who blew the trumpets,
        and the rear guard came after the ark, while they were blowing the trumpets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Joshua commanded the people, saying, \u201CYou will not shout,
        and you will not let your voice be heard; a word will not go out from your
        mouth until the day I say to you \u2018Shout!\u2019 Then you will shout.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the ark of Yahweh went around the city, circling once, and they
        came into the camp and spent the night in the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Joshua got up early in the morning, and the priests took up
        the ark of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The seven priests carrying the seven trumpets of the rams\u2019 horns
        before the ark of Yahweh went on continually, and they blew on the trumpets.
        And the armed men went before them, and the rear guard came after the ark
        of Yahweh, while the trumpets blew continually. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they marched around the city once on the second day, and they
        returned to the camp. They did this for six days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then on the seventh day they rose early at dawn, and they marched
        around the city in this manner seven times. It was only on that day that
        they marched around the city seven times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And at the seventh time the priests blew on the trumpets, and Joshua
        said to the people, \u201CShout! For Yahweh has given you the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The city and all that is in it will be devoted to Yahweh; only Rahab
        the prostitute and all who are with her in the house will live, because she
        hid the messengers whom we sent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'As for you, keep away from the things devoted to destruction so that
        you do not take them and bring about your own destruction, making the camp
        of Israel an object for destruction, bringing trouble upon it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But all of the silver and gold, and the items of bronze and iron,
        are holy to Yahweh, and they must go to Yahweh\u2019s treasury.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So the people shouted, and they blew on the trumpets. And when the
        people heard the sound of the trumpet, they raised a great shout, and the
        wall fell flat. The people charged, each one straight ahead into the city,
        and they captured it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And they utterly destroyed by the edge of the sword all who were
        in the city, both men and women, young and old, ox, sheep, and donkey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Joshua said to the two men who spied on the land, \u201CGo to
        the prostitute\u2019s house and bring out from there the woman and all who
        belong to her, just as you swore to her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So the young men who were spies went and brought Rahab and her father
        and mother, her brothers, and all who were with her. And they brought all
        her family out and set them outside the camp of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And they burned the city and all that was in it with fire; they put
        only the silver and gold, and the items of copper and iron, into the treasury
        of the house of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But Joshua spared Rahab the prostitute and her family and all who
        were with her, and she has lived in the midst of Israel until this day, because
        she hid the messengers whom Joshua sent to spy out Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Joshua swore at that time, saying, \u201CCursed is anyone before
        Yahweh who gets up and builds Jericho, this city. At the cost of his firstborn
        he will lay its foundation, and at the cost of his youngest he will set up
        its gates.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Yahweh was with Joshua, and his fame was in all the land. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sin of Achan'
      title: The Sin of Achan
      number: 1
      content: "But the Israelites broke faith concerning the devoted things. Achan
        son of Carmi son of Zabdi son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, took from
        the devoted things; and Yahweh\u2019s anger was kindled against the Israelites.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now Joshua sent men from Jericho to Ai, which is near Beth Aven,
        east of Bethel, and he said to them, \u201CGo up and spy out Ai.\u201D And
        the men went up and spied out Ai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they returned to Joshua and said to him, \u201CDo not let all
        the people go up and attack Ai; only two or three thousand men should go
        up because they are few. Do not make all the people weary up there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So about three thousand from the people went up there, and they fled
        before the men of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The men of Ai killed about thirty-six of them, and they chased them
        from the gate up to Shebarim and killed them on the slope. And the hearts
        of the people melted and became like water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Joshua tore his clothes and fell to the ground on his face before
        the ark of Yahweh until the evening, he and the elders of Israel; and they
        put dust on their heads.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201CAh, my Lord! Why did you bring this people
        across the Jordan to give us into the hand of the Amorites to destroy us?
        If only we had been content and stayed beyond the Jordan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Please, my Lord! What can I say after Israel has fled from its enemies?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The Canaanites and all the inhabitants of the land will hear of this,
        and they will surround us and cut off our name from the land. What will you
        do, for your great name?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Yahweh said to Joshua, \u201CStand up! Why have you fallen on
        your face? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Israel has sinned and transgressed my covenant that I commanded them.
        They have taken from the devoted things; they have stolen and acted deceitfully,
        and they have put them among their belongings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Israelites were unable to stand before their enemies; they fled
        from their enemies because they have become a thing devoted for destruction.
        I will be with you no more unless you destroy the devoted things from among
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Get up, sanctify the people, and say, \u2018Sanctify yourselves for
        tomorrow. Thus says Yahweh the God of Israel: \u201CThere are devoted things
        in your midst, O Israel. You will be unable to stand before you enemies until
        you remove the devoted things from your midst.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the morning you will come forward, tribe by tribe, and the tribe
        that Yahweh will select by lot will come forward by clans, and the clan that
        Yahweh selects by lot will come forward by families, and the family that
        Yahweh selects by lot will come forward one by one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The one caught with the devoted things will be burned with fire,
        he and all that belongs to him, because he transgressed the covenant of Yahweh,
        and because he did a disgraceful thing in Israel.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Joshua rose early in the morning and brought forward Israel, tribe
        by tribe, and the tribe of Judah was selected by lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he brought forward the clans of Judah and selected the clan of
        the Zerahites by lot. Then he brought forward the clan of the Zerahites,
        one by one, and Zabdi was selected by lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He brought forward his family, one by one, and Achan son of Carmi
        son of Zabdi son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, was selected by lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Joshua said to Achan, \u201CMy son, please, give glory to Yahweh
        the God of Israel, and give him a doxology in court. Tell me, please, what
        you have done; do not hide it from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Achan answered Joshua and said, \u201CIt is true. I have sinned
        against Yahweh the God of Israel, and this is what I did: "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I saw among the spoil a beautiful robe from Shinar, two hundred shekels
        of silver, and one bar of gold that weighed fifty shekels; I coveted them
        and took them. They are hidden in the ground inside my tent, and the silver
        is under it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Joshua sent messengers, and they ran to the tent; and there they
        were, hidden in his tent, and the silver was under it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they took them from the tent and brought them to Joshua and all
        the Israelites. And they spread them out before the presence of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Joshua, and all Israel with him, took Achan son of Zerah, the
        silver, the robe, the bar of gold, his sons and daughters, his cattle and
        donkeys, his sheep, his tent, and everything that was his, and they brought
        them to the valley of Achor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201CWhy did you bring us trouble? Yahweh will
        bring you trouble on this day.\u201D And all Israel stoned them with stones;
        and they burned them with fire after they stoned them with stones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then they placed on top of him a great pile of stones that remains
        to this day. And Yahweh turned from his burning anger, and thus the name
        of that place to this day is called the valley of Achor.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ai Is Destroyed'
      title: Ai Is Destroyed
      number: 1
      content: "Then Yahweh said to Joshua, \u201CDo not fear or be dismayed. Take
        all the fighting men with you and go up immediately to Ai. Look, I am giving
        into your hand the king of Ai, his city, and his land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "You will do to Ai and its king that which you did to Jericho and
        its king; you may take only its spoils and livestock as booty for yourself.
        Set for yourself an ambush against the city from behind it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Joshua and all the fighting men went up immediately to Ai. Joshua
        chose thirty thousand of the best fighting men and sent them by night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he commanded them, saying, \u201CLook, you are to lay an ambush
        against the city from behind. Do not go very far from the city and be ready. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then I and all of the people who are with me will approach the city.
        And when they go out to meet us as before, we will flee from them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They will come out after us until we draw them away from the city,
        because they will think, \u2018They are fleeing from us as before.\u2019
        So we will flee from them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then you will rise up from the ambush and take possession of the
        city, for Yahweh your God will give it into your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And when you capture the city you will set it on fire as Yahweh commanded.
        Look, I have commanded you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Joshua sent them out, and they went to the place of the ambush,
        and they sat between Bethel and Ai, to the west of Ai; but Joshua spent the
        night with the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Joshua rose early in the morning and mustered the people, and he
        went up with the elders of Israel before the people of Ai.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'All the fighting men who were with him went up and drew near before
        the city and camped north of Ai; there was a valley between him and Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he took about five thousand men and set them in ambush between
        Bethel and Ai, to the west of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So they stationed the forces; all the army was north of the city
        while the rear guard was west. But Joshua went that night to the middle of
        the valley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When the king of Ai saw this, the men of the city hurried and rose
        early and went out to meet Israel for battle\u2014he and all his army\u2014to
        the meeting place before the Arabah. He did not know that there was an ambush
        for him behind the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel acted like they were beaten before them,
        and they fled in the direction of the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'All of the people who were in the city were called to pursue after
        them. As they pursued after Joshua, they were drawn away from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Not a man remained in Ai or Bethel who had not gone out after Israel;
        they left the city open and pursued after Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Yahweh said to Joshua, \u201CStretch out the sword that is in
        your hand to Ai, because I will give it into your hand.\u201D And Joshua
        stretched out the sword that was in his hand to the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The moment he stretched out his hand, those in the ambush stood up
        quickly from their place and ran. And they went into the city and captured
        it, quickly setting the city ablaze with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then the men of Ai looked behind them, and they saw smoke from the
        city rising to the sky; they had no power to flee this way or that, and the
        people fleeing the wilderness turned around to the pursuers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Joshua and all Israel saw that the ambush had captured the city
        and that the smoke of the city was rising; they returned and struck down
        the men of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the others from the city came out to meet them, and they found
        themselves surrounded by Israel, some on one side, and others on the other
        side. And they struck them down until no survivor or fugitive was left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But they captured the king of Ai alive, and they brought him to Joshua. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Israel finished slaughtering all the inhabitants of Ai in the
        open field, in the wilderness where they pursued them, and when all of them
        had fallen by the edge of the sword until they all had perished, all Israel
        returned to Ai and attacked it with the edge of the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "All the people that fell on that day, both men and women, were twelve
        thousand\u2014all the inhabitants of Ai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For Joshua did not draw back his hand that was stretched out with
        the sword until he had utterly destroyed all the inhabitants of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Only the livestock and the spoil of that city Israel took as booty
        for themselves, according to the word of Yahweh that Joshua commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Joshua burned Ai and made it an everlasting heap of rubbish, a
        desolate place until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Israel Renews the Covenant'
      title: Israel Renews the Covenant
      number: 29
      content: 'The king of Ai he hanged on a tree until the time of evening, and
        as the sun went down Joshua commanded them, and they brought down his dead
        body from the tree. Then they threw it at the entrance of the gate of the
        city, and they raised over it a great heap of stones that remains to this
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Joshua built an altar on Mount Ebal for Yahweh the God of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "as Moses Yahweh\u2019s servant commanded the Israelites, as it is
        written in the scroll of the law of Moses: \u201Can altar of unhewn stones
        on which no one has wielded an iron implement.\u201D And they offered burnt
        offerings on it and sacrificed fellowship offerings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And there Joshua wrote on the stones a copy of the law of Moses,
        which he had written, in the presence of the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then all Israel, foreigner as well as native, with the elders, officials,
        and judges stood on either side of the ark before the priests and the Levites,
        who carried the ark of the covenant of Yahweh. Half of them stood in front
        of Mount Gerizim, and the other half in front of Mount Ebal, as Moses Yahweh\u2019s
        servant had commanded before to bless the people of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And afterward he read all the words of the law, the blessings and
        the curses, according to all that was written in the scroll of the law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'There was not a word from all that Moses commanded that Joshua did
        not read before the assembly of all Israel, and the women, the little children,
        and the traveling foreigners among them. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Gibeonites Act with Cunning'
      title: The Gibeonites Act with Cunning
      number: 1
      content: "Now when all the kings who were beyond the Jordan in the hill country
        and in the Shephelah, and on all the coast of the great sea toward Lebanon\u2014the
        Hittites, the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and
        the Jebusites\u2014heard of this, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'they gathered themselves together to fight with one accord against
        Joshua and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But the inhabitants of Gibeon heard what Joshua did to Jericho and
        Ai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and they acted on their part with cunning: they went and prepared
        provisions, and took worn-out sacks for their donkeys and old wineskins that
        were torn and mended. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sandals on their feet were patched and old, their clothes were
        old, and their food was dry and crumbled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And they went to Joshua at the camp at Gilgal and said to him and
        to the men of Israel, \u201CWe have come from a far land; so then make a
        covenant with us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the men of Israel said to the Hivites, \u201CPerhaps you are
        living among us; how can we make a covenant with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They said to Joshua, \u201CWe are your servants.\u201D And Joshua
        said to them, \u201CWho are you, and from where do you come?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CYour servants have come from a very far
        land because of the name of Yahweh your God; we have heard of his reputation,
        of all that he did in Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and of all that he did to the two kings of the Amorites who were
        beyond the Jordan\u2014to Sihon king of Heshbon and to Og king of Bashan,
        who was in Ashtaroth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So our elders said to us and all the inhabitants of our land, \u2018Take
        in your hand provisions for the journey, and go to meet them, and say to
        them, \u201CWe are your servants; so then make a covenant with us.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'This is our bread; it was hot when we took it from our houses as
        provisions on the day we set out to come to you. But now, look, it is dry
        and crumbled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "These are the wineskins that we filled new, but look, they have burst;
        and these are our clothes and sandals that have worn out from the very long
        journey.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the leaders took from their provisions, but they did not ask direction
        from Yahweh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Joshua made peace with them, and he made a covenant with them
        to allow them to live happily, and the leaders of the congregation swore
        an oath to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And it happened that at the end of three days, after they made a
        covenant with them, they heard that they were their neighbors and living
        among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the Israelites set out and went to their cities on the third
        day (their cities were Gibeon, Kephirah, Beeroth, and Kiriath Jearim). '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But the Israelites did not attack them, because the leaders of the
        congregation had sworn to them by Yahweh the God of Israel. And all the congregation
        murmured against their leaders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But all the leaders of the congregation said, \u201CWe have sworn
        to them by Yahweh the God of Israel, and so we cannot touch them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "This we will do to them: we will let them live so that wrath will
        not be on us because of the oath we swore to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the leaders said to them, \u201CLet them live.\u201D So they
        became woodcutters and water carriers for all the congregation, just as the
        leaders had said to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Joshua summoned them and said, \u201CWhy have you deceived us
        saying, \u2018We are very far from you\u2019 when you are living among us? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Therefore you are cursed; some of you will always be slaves as woodcutters
        and water carriers for the house of my God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And they answered Joshua and said, \u201CBecause it was told with
        certainty to your servants that Yahweh your God commanded Moses his servant
        to give to you all the land and to destroy all the inhabitants of the land
        before you, so we were very afraid for our lives because of you, and so we
        did this thing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So then, look, we are in your hand; do with us whatever seems good
        and right in your eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So he did this to them: he saved them from the hand of the Israelites,
        and they did not kill them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And that day Joshua made them woodcutters and water carriers for
        the congregation and for the altar of Yahweh, to this day, in the place that
        he should choose. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sun Stands Still at Gibeon'
      title: The Sun Stands Still at Gibeon
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened that when Adoni-Zedek king of Jerusalem heard that
        Joshua captured Ai and had utterly destroyed it (just as he had done to Jericho
        and its king, so he did to Ai and its king) and that the inhabitants of Gibeon
        had made peace with Israel and were among them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'he became very afraid because Gibeon was a very large city, like
        one of the royal cities, and because it was larger than Ai, and all its men
        were mighty warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Adoni-Zedek king of Jerusalem sent word to Hohman king of Hebron,
        to Piram king of Jarmuth, to Japhia king of Lachish, and to Debir king of
        Eglon, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CCome up and help me, and let us attack Gibeon, because it has
        made peace with Joshua and the Israelites.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the five kings of the Amorites, the king of Jerusalem, the king
        of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon,
        gathered together and went up, they and all their forces, and they laid siege
        to Gibeon and made war against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the men of Gibeon sent word to Joshua at the camp at Gilgal,
        saying, \u201CDo not abandon your servant. Come up to us quickly and save
        us! Help us, for all the kings of the Amorites who dwell in the hill country
        have gathered against us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joshua went up from Gilgal, he and all the fighting men with him,
        all the best warriors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Yahweh said to Joshua, \u201CDo not be afraid of them, for I
        have given them into your hand; no one will withstand you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Joshua came upon them suddenly by marching up all night from Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Yahweh threw them into panic before Israel, who struck them with
        a great blow at Gibeon and pursued them by the way of the ascent of Beth-horon
        and struck them as far as Azekah and Makkedah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And as they were fleeing from Israel, they were on the slope of Beth-horon,
        and Yahweh threw huge stones from the heavens on them as far as Azekah; and
        more died by the hail stones than those whom the Israelites killed by the
        sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Joshua spoke to Yahweh, on the day Yahweh gave the Amorites
        over to the Israelites, and he said in the sight of Israel, \u201CSun in
        Gibeon, stand still, and moon, in the valley of Aijalon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the sun stood still, and the moon stopped, until the nation took
        vengeance on its enemies. Is it not written in the scroll of Jashar? The
        sun stood still in the middle of the heaven and was not in haste to set for
        about a full day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'There has not been a day like this before it or after, that Yahweh
        listened to the voice of a man; for Yahweh fought for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Kings of the Amorites Are Killed'
      title: The Kings of the Amorites Are Killed
      number: 15
      content: 'And Joshua returned and all Israel with him to the camp at Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But these five kings fled and hid themselves in the cave at Makkedah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And it was told to Joshua, saying, \u201CThe five kings were found
        hidden in the cave at Makkedah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201CRoll large stones against the mouth of the
        cave, and set men in front of it to guard them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But do not stay there; pursue after your enemies and attack them
        from the rear. Do not allow them to go into their cities, for Yahweh your
        God has given them into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When Joshua and the Israelites had finished striking them with a
        very great blow, until they perished, those of them who survived went into
        the fortified cities, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and all the people returned to the camp safely to Joshua at Makkedah.
        No one spoke against the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201COpen the mouth of the cave, and bring to me
        those five kings from the cave.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they did so, and brought him these five kings from the cave,
        the king of Jerusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king
        of Lachish, and the king of Eglon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And when they brought these kings to Joshua, Joshua called all the
        men of Israel and said to the commanders of the fighting men who had gone
        with him, \u201CCome near, put your feet on the necks of these kings.\u201D
        So they came near and put their feet on their necks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Joshua said to them, \u201CDo not be afraid or dismayed! Be strong
        and bold, for thus Yahweh will do to all your enemies whom you are about
        to fight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And after this Joshua struck them down and killed them, and he hanged
        them on five trees. And they were hanging on the trees until the evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And it happened at the time of sunset, Joshua commanded, and they
        took them down from the trees and threw them into the cave where they had
        hidden themselves, and they put large stones against the mouth of the cave,
        which are there to this very day. '
      comments: []
    - name: "28: Joshua\u2019s Conquest of the South"
      title: "Joshua\u2019s Conquest of the South"
      number: 28
      content: 'Joshua captured Makkedah on that day, and he struck it and its king
        with the edge of the sword; he utterly destroyed it and everyone that was
        in it. He did not leave behind a survivor. So he did to the king of Makkedah
        just as he did to the king of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And Joshua passed on, and all of Israel with him, from Makkedah to
        Libnah, and he fought against Libnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Yahweh also gave it into the hand of Israel, and its king and
        all the people in it he struck with the edge of the sword. He left in it
        no survivor. He did to its king just as he did to the king of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And Joshua passed on, and all of Israel with him, from Libnah to
        Lachish, and he laid siege to it and fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And Yahweh gave Lachish into the hand of Israel, and he captured
        it on the second day. He struck it with the edge of the sword, and everyone
        in it, just as he did to Libnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then Horam king of Gezer came up to help Lachish, and Joshua struck
        him and his people until he left no survivor behind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And Joshua passed on, and all of Israel with him, from Lachish to
        Eglon, and they laid siege to it and fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And they captured it on that day, and he struck it with the edge
        of the sword, and all the people that were in it on that day he utterly destroyed
        as he had done to Lachish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And Joshua went up, and all Israel with him, from Eglon to Hebron,
        and they fought against it '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'and captured it, and they struck it with the edge of the sword, its
        king and all its cities, and all the people that were in it; he left behind
        no survivor, as he had done to Eglon, and he utterly destroyed it and all
        the people that were in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then Joshua returned to Debir, and all of Israel with him, and they
        fought against it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and he captured it and its king and all its cities, and they struck
        them with the the edge of the sword, and they utterly destroyed all the people
        that were in it; he left behind no survivor, just as he had done to Hebron.
        Thus he did to Debir and its king what he had done to Libnah and its king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "So Joshua struck all the land\u2014the hill country, the Negev, the
        Shephelah, and the slopes\u2014and all their kings; he left behind no survivor,
        and all that breathed he utterly destroyed as Yahweh the God of Israel commanded. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Joshua struck them from Kadesh Barnea to Gaza, and all the land of
        Goshen up to Gibeon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'all of these kings and their land Joshua captured at one time, because
        Yahweh the God of Israel fought for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joshua\u2019s Conquest of the North"
      title: "Joshua\u2019s Conquest of the North"
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened, when Jabin king of Hazor heard this, he sent to
        Jobab king of Madon, to the king of Shimron, to the king of Acshaph, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and to the kings who were in the north in the hill country, in the
        Arabah south of Kinnereth, in the Shephelah, and in Naphoth Dor in the west, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'to the Canaanites in the east and west, the Amorites, the Hittites,
        the Perizzites, and the Jebusites in the hill country, and the Hivites at
        the foot of Hermon in the land of Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They came out, they and all their armies with them, as a great army
        like the sand on the seashore, with very many horses and chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And all these kings joined forces, and they came and camped together
        by the waters of Merom to fight with Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Yahweh said to Joshua, \u201CDo not be afraid because of their
        presence, for tomorrow at this time I will hand them over slain to Israel;
        you will hamstring their horses and burn their chariots with fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joshua, and all the fighting men with him, came against them suddenly
        at the waters of Merom, and they attacked them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Yahweh gave them into the hand of Israel, and they struck them
        and pursued them up to Great Sidon and Misrephoth Maim, and eastward up to
        the valley of Mizpeh. And they struck them until they left behind no survivor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Joshua did to them as Yahweh commanded him; he hamstrung their
        horses and burned their chariots with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Joshua turned back at that time, and he captured Hazor and struck
        its king with the sword, because Hazor formerly was the head of all these
        kingdoms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He struck all the people that were in it with the edge of the sword,
        utterly destroying them. There was no one left who breathed, and he burned
        Hazor with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Joshua captured all the cities of these kings, and all their
        kings, and he utterly destroyed them with the edge of the sword, as Moses
        the servant of Yahweh commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Israel did not burn the cities standing on their mounds, except Hazor
        alone, which Joshua burned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And all the spoil and livestock of these cities the Israelites took
        as booty; they struck the people with the edge of the sword, until they had
        destroyed them\u2014they left behind no one who breathed. "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: A Review of Joshua\u2019s Conquests"
      title: "A Review of Joshua\u2019s Conquests"
      number: 15
      content: 'Just as Yahweh commanded Moses his servant, so Moses commanded Joshua,
        and Joshua did; he left nothing undone that Yahweh had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Joshua took all this land: the hill country, all the Negev, all
        the land of Goshen, the Shephelah, the Arabah, and the hill country of Israel
        and its Shephelah,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'from Mount Halak that rises to Seir and to Baal Gad in the valley
        of Lebanon at the foot of Mount Hermon; he captured all their kings, struck
        them, and killed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For many days Joshua made war with all these kings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "There was not a city that made peace with the Israelites besides
        the Hivites and the inhabitants of Gibeon\u2014all were taken in battle.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For it was Yahweh that hardened their hearts, to meet Israel in war
        in order to utterly destroy them without mercy, that they would destroy them
        just as Yahweh commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'At that time Joshua came and exterminated the Anakites from the hill
        country, from Hebron, Debir, Anab, and from all the hill country of Judah,
        and from all the hill country of Israel; Joshua utterly destroyed them with
        their cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'None of the Anakites were left in the land of the Israelites; some
        remained only in Gaza, Gath, and Ashdod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Joshua took all the land according to all that Yahweh had spoken
        to Moses; and Joshua gave it as an inheritance to Israel, according to their
        tribal divisions, and the land rested from war. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Kings Conquered by Joshua'
      title: The Kings Conquered by Joshua
      number: 1
      content: 'These are the kings of the land whom the Israelites defeated, and
        of whose land they took possession beyond the Jordon to the east, from the
        wadi of Arnon up to Mount Hermon, and all the Arabah to the east: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived in Heshbon, and ruled from
        Aroer, which is on the edge of the wadi of Arnon, from the middle of the
        valley and half of Gilead, up to the Jabbok River, which marks the border
        of the Ammonites;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the Arabah up to the Kinnereth Sea to the east, and as far as
        the sea of Arabah, the Salt Sea to the east, in the direction of Beth Jeshimoth,
        and to the area southward, at the foot of the slopes of Pisgah;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'the territory of Og king of Bashan, one of the last of the Rephaites,
        who lived at Ashtaroth and Edrei '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and ruled over Mount Hermon and Salecah and over all Bashan up to
        the border of the Geshurites and the Maacathites, and half of Gilead, as
        far as the border of Sihon king of Heshbon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: The Kings Conquered by Moses'
      title: The Kings Conquered by Moses
      number: 6
      content: "Moses Yahweh\u2019s servant and the Israelites defeated them; and
        Moses Yahweh\u2019s servant gave it as a possession to the Reubenites, the
        Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'These are the kings of the land whom Joshua and the Israelites defeated
        beyond to the Jordan to the west, from Baal Gad in the valley of Lebanon,
        and up to Mount Halak, which rises to Seir. And Joshua gave it as a possession
        to the tribes of Israel according to their allotments, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'in the hill country, the Shephelah, the Arabah, on the slopes, in
        the wilderness, and in the Negev; the Hittites, the Amorites, the Canaanites,
        the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the king of Jericho, one; the king of Ai, which is beside Bethel,
        one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the king of Jerusalem, one; the king of Hebron, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the king of Jarmuth, one; the king of Lachish, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the king of Eglon, one; the king of Gezer, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the king of Debir, one; the king of Geder, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the king of Hormah, one; the king of Arad, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the king of Libnah, one; the king of Adullam, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the king of Makkedah, one; the king of Bethel, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the king of Tappuah, one; the king of Hepher, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the king of Aphek, one; the king of Lasharon, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the king of Madon, one; the king of Hazor, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the king of Shimron-meron, one; the king of Acshaph, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the king of Taanach, one; the king of Megiddo, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'the king of Kedesh, one; the king of Jokneam in Carmel, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'the king of Dor in Naphath Dor, one; the king of Goiim for Gilgal,
        one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'the king of Tirzah, one; all the kings, thirty-one. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Land Still Remains to be Conquered'
      title: Land Still Remains to be Conquered
      number: 1
      content: "Now Joshua was old and advanced in years, and Yahweh said to him,
        \u201CYou are old and advanced in years, and very much of the land remains
        to be possessed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'This is the remaining land: all the regions of the Philistines, and
        all of the Geshurites,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'from the Shihor, which is east of Egypt, up to the border of Ekron
        to the north, which is reckoned as Canaanite; there are five Philistine rulers:
        the Gazites, Ashdodites, Ashkelonites, Gittites, Ekronites, and the Avvim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In the south; all the land of the Canaanites, and Mearah, which belongs
        to the Sidonians up to Aphek, to the border of the Amorites,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and the land of the Gebalites, and all the Lebanon, toward the east,
        from Baal Gad at the foot of Mount Hermon up to Lebo-Hamath; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'all the inhabitants of the hill country, from the Lebanon up to Misrephoth
        Maim, and all the Sidonians. I will drive them out from before the Israelites;
        only allocate it to Israel as an inheritance just as I have commanded you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore, divide this land as an inheritance to the nine tribes
        and the half-tribe of Manasseh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "With it the Reubenites, and the Gadites received their inheritance,
        which Moses gave them beyond the Jordan to the east, just as Moses Yahweh\u2019s
        servant gave to them: "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'from Aroer, which is on the edge of the wadi of Arnon, and the city
        which is in the middle of the wadi, and all the plateau from Medeba up to
        Dibon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and all the cities of Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in
        Heshbon up to the border of the Ammonites;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and Gilead, and the border of the Geshurite and the Maacathites,
        all of Mount Hermon, and Bashan up to Salecah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "all the kingdom of Og in Bashan, who reigned in Ashtaroth and Edrei\u2014he
        was left over from the survivors of the Rephaim; these Moses had defeated
        and driven out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the Israelites did not drive out the Geshurites or the Maacathites;
        Geshur and Maacah live among Israel to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Reuben\u2019s Inheritance"
      title: "Reuben\u2019s Inheritance"
      number: 14
      content: 'Only the tribe of Levites Moses did not give an inheritance; the
        offerings made by fire to Yahweh the God of Israel are their inheritance,
        just as he promised to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Moses gave an inheritance to the tribe of the descendants of Reuben
        according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Their territory was from Aroer, which was on the edge of the wadi
        of Arnon, and the city that is in the middle of the valley, and all the plateau
        by Medeba; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Heshbon and its cities that are on the plateau; Dibon, Bamoth Baal,
        Beth Baal Meon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Jahaz, Kedemoth, Mephaath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Kiriathaim, Sibmah, and Zereth Shahar on the hill of the valley; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Beth Peor, the slopes of Pisgah, and Beth Jeshimoth; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'all of the cities of the plateau, and all the kingdom of Sihon king
        of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon and whom Moses defeated with the
        leaders of Midian, Evi, Rekem, Zur, Hur, and Reba, the princes of Sihon who
        dwelled in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In addition to their slain, the Israelites killed with the sword
        Balaam son of Beor, who practiced divination. '
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Gad\u2019s Inheritance"
      title: "Gad\u2019s Inheritance"
      number: 23
      content: 'And the border of the descendants of Reuben was the Jordan and its
        banks. This was the inheritance of the descendants of Reuben according to
        their families, the cities, and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Moses gave an inheritance to the tribe of Gad, to the descendants
        of Gad, according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Their territory was Jazer and all the cities of Gilead, and half
        the land of the Ammonites up to Aroer, which is east of Rabbah;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and from Heshbon up to Ramah-Mizpeh and Betonim, and from Mahanaim
        up to the territory to Debir; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'in the valley of Beth Haram, Beth Nimrah, Succoth, Zaphon, and the
        rest of the kingdom of Sihon king of Heshbon, the Jordan and its banks, up
        to the lower end of the Kinnereth Sea beyond the Jordan to the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: "28: The Half-Tribe of Manasseh\u2019s Inheritance"
      title: "The Half-Tribe of Manasseh\u2019s Inheritance"
      number: 28
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the Gadites according to their families,
        the cities, and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Moses gave an inheritance to the half-tribe of Manasseh; it was for
        the half-tribe of the descendants of Manasseh according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Their territory was from Mahanaim, all Bashan, all the kingdom of
        Og king of Bashan, and all the settlements of Jair, which are in Bashan,
        sixty cities, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and half of Gilead, with Ashtaroth, Edrei, and the cities of the
        kingdom of Og in Bashan; these were allotted to the children of Makir son
        of Manasseh, for half of the children of Makir according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'These are the territories that Moses gave as an inheritance on the
        desert-plateau of Moab, beyond the Jordan, east of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'But to the tribe of Levi Moses did not give an inheritance; Yahweh
        the God of Israel, he is their inheritance, just as he promised them.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Land Allotted West of the Jordan'
      title: The Land Allotted West of the Jordan
      number: 1
      content: 'These are the territories that the Israelites inherited in the land
        of Canaan, which Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of Nun, and the heads of
        the families of the tribes of the Israelites gave as an inheritance to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Their inheritance was by lot, just as Yahweh commanded through the
        hand of Moses, for the nine tribes and the half-tribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For Moses had given an inheritance of the two tribes and the half-tribe
        beyond the Jordan, but to the Levites he gave no inheritance among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the descendants of Joseph were two tribes, Manasseh and Ephraim,
        and they did not give a plot of ground to the Levites in the land, only cities
        to live in, with their pastureland for their flocks and for their goods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Caleb Receives Hebron'
      title: Caleb Receives Hebron
      number: 5
      content: 'Just as Yahweh commanded Moses, so the Israelites did; and they allotted
        the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the descendants of Judah came to Joshua at Gilgal; and Caleb
        son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite said to him, \u201CYou know the word that
        Yahweh said to Moses the man of God at Kadesh Barnea concerning you and me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I was forty years old when Moses Yahweh\u2019s servant sent me from
        Kadesh Barnea to spy out the land, and I returned with an honest report.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'My companions who went up with me made the hearts of the people melt,
        but I remained true to Yahweh my God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Moses swore on that day, saying, \u2018Surely the land that your
        foot has trodden on will be an inheritance to you and your sons forever,
        because you remained true to Yahweh my God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So then, look, Yahweh has kept me alive just as he promised these
        forty-five years, from the time that Yahweh spoke this word to Moses while
        Israel wandered in the wilderness. Now look, today I am eighty-five years
        old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Today I am still strong, just as on the day that Moses sent me; as
        my strength was then, so now also is my strength for war and for daily activities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So now give me this hill country that Yahweh spoke of on that day,
        for you heard on that day that the Anakites were there, with great and fortified
        cities. Perhaps Yahweh is with me, and I will drive them out just as Yahweh
        promised.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Joshua blessed him and gave Hebron to Caleb son of Jephunneh
        as an inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Thus Hebron became the inheritance of Caleb son of Jephunneh the
        Kenizzite to this day, because he remained true to Yahweh the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the name of Hebron formerly was Kiriath Arba; Arba was the greatest
        person among the Anakites. And the land rested from war. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Allotment of Judah'
      title: The Allotment of Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'The allotment for the tribe of the descendants of Judah according
        to their families reached to the border of Edom, to the wilderness of Zin,
        to the far south.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Their southern border was from the end of the Salt Sea, from the
        bay facing southward; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'it continues to the south to the ascent of Akrabbim, passes along
        to Zin, it goes up south of Kadesh Barnea, passes along Hezron, goes up to
        Addar, and makes a turn to Karka; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'it passes on to Azmon, continues by the wadi of Egypt, and it ends
        at the sea. This will be your southern border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The eastern border is the Salt Sea up to the mouth of the Jordan.
        The border on the northern side runs from the bay of the sea at the mouth
        of the Jordan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'the border goes up to Beth-hoglah and passes along north of Beth
        Arabah; and the border goes up the stone of Bohan son of Reuben; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and the border goes up to Debir from the valley of Achor, and to
        the north, turning to Gilgal, which is opposite the ascent of Adummim, which
        is south of the wadi; and the border passes on to the waters of En Shemesh,
        and it ends at En Rogel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the border goes up by the Valley of Ben Hinnom to the slope
        of the Jebusites from the south (that is, Jerusalem); and the border goes
        up to the top of the mountain that lies opposite the valley of Hinnom to
        the west, which is at the end of the valley of Rephaim to the north; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'then the border turns from the top of the mountain to the spring
        of the waters of Nephtoah, and continues from there to the cities of Mount
        Ephron; the border then turns to Baalah (that is, Kiriath Jearim); '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and the border goes around from Baalah to the west, to Mount Seir,
        and passes on to the slope of Mount Jearim from the north (that is, Kesalon),
        and goes down to Beth Shemesh, and passes along by Timnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The border continues to the slope of Ekron to the north, then bends
        around to Shikkeron, it passes on to Mount Baalah and continues to Jabneel;
        and the border ends at the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the western border is to the Great Sea and its coast. This is
        the border surrounding the descendants of Judah according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "According to the commandment of Yahweh to Joshua, he gave to Caleb
        son of Jephunneh a plot of ground among the descendants of Judah, Kiriath
        Arba, which is Hebron (Arba was Anak\u2019s father). "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Caleb drove out from there three of Anak\u2019s sons, Sheshai, Ahiman,
        and Talmai, the descendants of Anak. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And from there he went up against the inhabitants of Debir (the former
        name of Debir was Kiriath Sepher). '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Caleb said, \u201CWhoever attacks Kiriath Sepher and captures
        it, I will give to him my daughter Acsah as a wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Othniel son of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb, captured it, and he gave
        to him Acsah his daughter as a wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When she came to him she urged him to ask her father for a field.
        So she dismounted from the donkey, and Caleb said to her, \u201CWhat do you
        want?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Cities of Judah'
      title: The Cities of Judah
      number: 19
      content: "And she said to him, \u201CGive to me a gift; you have given me the
        land of the Negev, and you must give to me a spring of water.\u201D And he
        gave to her the upper and lower spring.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the tribe of the descendants of Judah
        according to their families: '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the cities belonging to the tribe of the descendants of Judah to
        the far south, to the border of Edom to the south, were Kabzeel, Eder, Jagur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Kinah, Dimonah, Adadah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Kedesh, Hazor, Ithnan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Ziph, Telem, Bealoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Hazor Hadattah, Kerioth Hezron (that is, Hazor), '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Amam, Shema, Moladah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Hazar Gaddah, Heshmon, Beth Pelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Hazar Shual, Beersheba, Biziothiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Baalah, Iim, Ezem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Eltolad, Kesil, Hormah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Ziklag, Madmannah, Sansannah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Lebaoth, Shilhim, Ain, and Rimmon; in all, twenty-nine cities and
        their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'In the Shephelah: Eshtaol, Zorah, Ashnah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Zanoah, En Gannim, Tappuah, Enam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Jarmuth, Adullam, Socoh, Azekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Shaaraim, Adithaim, Gederah, and Gederothaim; fourteen cities and
        their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zenan, Hadashah, Migdal Gad, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Dilean, Mizpah, Joktheel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Lachish, Bozkath, Eglon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Cabbon, Lahma, Kitlish, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Gederoth, Beth Dagon, Naamah, and Makkedah; sixteen cities and their
        villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Libnah, Ether, Ashan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Jephthah, Ashnah, Nezib, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Keilah, Aczib, and Mareshah; nine cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Ekron, its towns and villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'from Ekron to the sea, and all that were near Ashdod and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Ashdod, its towns and villages; Gaza, its towns and villages, up
        to the wadi of Egypt and the Great Sea and its coast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And in the hill country: Shamir, Jattir, Socoh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Dannah, Kiriath Sanna (that is, Debir), '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Anab, Eshtemoh, Anim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Goshen, Holon, and Giloh; eleven cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Arab, Dumah, Eshan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Janim, Beth-tappuah, Aphekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Humtah, Kiriath Arba (that is, Hebron), and Zior; nine cities and
        their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'Moan, Carmel, Ziph, Juttah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'Jezreel, Jokdeam, Zanoah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'Kain, Gibeah, and Timnah; ten cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'Halhul, Beth Zur, Gedor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Maarath, Beth Anoth, and Eltekon; six cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'Kiriath Baal (that is, Kiriath Jearim) and Rabbah; two cities and
        their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'In the wilderness: Beth Arabah, Middin, Secacah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Nibshan, the city of Salt, and En Gedi; six cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'But the descendants of Judah were unable to drive out the Jebusites,
        the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so the Jebusites live with the descendants
        of Judah in Jerusalem to this day. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Allotment of Ephraim and Manasseh'
      title: The Allotment of Ephraim and Manasseh
      number: 1
      content: 'The allotment of the descendants of Joseph went from the Jordan by
        Jericho, at the waters of Jericho to the east, into the wilderness, going
        up from Jericho into the hill country to Bethel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'it continues from Bethel to Luz, and it passes along to the territory
        of the Arkites at Ataroth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then it goes down, to the west, to the territory of the Japhletites,
        up to the territory of Lower Beth-horon, then to Gezer, and it ends at the
        sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the descendants of Joseph, Manasseh and Ephraim, received their
        inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'This was the border of the descendants of Ephraim according to their
        families: the border of their inheritance to the east was Ataroth Addar,
        up to Upper Beth-horon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The border continues to the sea; from Micmethath to the north, the
        border turns to the east to Taanath Shiloh, and it passes along it from the
        east to Janoah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then it goes down from Janoah to Ataroth and to Naarah; it touches
        Jericho and ends at the Jordan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'from Tappuah the border goes to the west, to the wadi of Kanah, and
        it ends at the sea. This is the inheritance of the tribe of the descendants
        of Ephraim according to their families, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'with the cities that were set apart for the descendants of Ephraim
        in the midst of the inheritance of the descendants of Manasseh, all the cities
        and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But they did not drive out the Canananites who were dwelling in Gezer,
        and so the Canaanites live in the midst of Ephraim to this day, but they
        became forced laborers. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Allotment of the Other Half-Tribe of Manasseh'
      title: The Allotment of the Other Half-Tribe of Manasseh
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the allotment was made for the tribe of Manasseh, because he
        was the firstborn of Joseph. To Makir, the firstborn of Manasseh, the father
        of Gilead, were allotted Gilead and Bashan, because he was a warrior.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "An allotment was made for the remaining descendants of Manasseh,
        according to their families: For the children of Abiezer, Helek, Asriel,
        Shechem, Hepher, and Shemida\u2014these were the male descendants of Manasseh
        son of Joseph according to their families. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But Zelophehad son of Hepher, son of Gilead, son of Makir, son of
        Manasseh, had no sons, only daughters. These are the names of his daughters:
        Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They came before Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of Nun, and the leaders,
        saying, \u201CYahweh commanded Moses to give an inheritance to us among our
        kinsmen.\u201D Therefore, according to the command of Yahweh he gave them
        an inheritance among the kinsmen of their father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thus ten shares fell to Manasseh, besides the land of Gilead and
        Bashan, which is beyond the Jordan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'because the daughters of Manasseh received an inheritance among his
        sons. And the land of Gilead was allotted to the remaining descendants of
        Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The border of Manasseh was from Asher to Micmethath, which is opposite
        Shechem; then the border goes to the south, to the inhabitants of En Tappuah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The land of Tappuah belonged to Manasseh, but Tuppuah on the border
        of Manasseh belonged to the descendants of Ephraim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the border goes down to the wadi of Kanah to the south of the
        wadi. These cities belong to Ephraim among the cities of Manasseh. The border
        of Manasseh is north of the wadi, and it ends at the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The south is Ephraim\u2019s, and the north is Manasseh\u2019s; the
        sea is their border; Asher touches the north and on the east Issachar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'In Issachar and Asher, Manasseh had Beth-shean and its villages,
        Ibleam and its villages, the inhabitants of Dor and its villages, the inhabitants
        of En-dor and its villages, the inhabitants of Taanach and its villages,
        the inhabitants of Megiddo and its villages; the third is Napheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the descendants of Manasseh were not able to take possession
        of these towns; the Canaanites were determined to live in this land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Tribes of Joseph Object'
      title: The Tribes of Joseph Object
      number: 13
      content: 'And it happened, when the Israelites grew strong, they put the Canaanites
        to forced labor but never drove them out completely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The descendants of Joseph spoke with Joshua, saying, \u201CWhy have
        you given us one allotment and one share as an inheritance? We are many people,
        which Yahweh has blessed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Joshua said to them, \u201CIf you are many people, go up to the
        forest and clear a place there for yourselves in the land of the Perizzites
        and Rephaim, since the hill country of Ephraim is too narrow for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the descendants of Joseph said, \u201CThe hill country is not
        enough for us, and all of the Canaanites living in the land of the valley
        have chariots of iron, those in Beth-shean and its villages, and those in
        the Jezreel Valley.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Joshua said to the house of Joseph, to Ephraim and Manasseh,
        \u201CYou are many people and have great power; you will not have one allotment
        only; "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "the hill country will be yours. Even though it is a forest, you will
        clear it, and it will be yours to its farthest borders. You will drive out
        the Canaanites, even though they have iron chariots and are strong.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Last of the Land Is Divided'
      title: The Last of the Land Is Divided
      number: 1
      content: 'The entire congregation of the Israelites assembled at Shiloh, and
        they set up there the tent of meeting, and the land was subdued before them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And seven tribes remained among the Israelites who had not been apportioned
        their inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Joshua said to the Israelites, \u201CHow long will you be slack
        about going to take possession of the land that Yahweh, the God of your ancestors,
        has given you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Provide three men from each tribe, and I will send them so that they
        may begin to go through the land and write a description of it according
        to their inheritance, and let them come to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They will divide it among themselves into seven portions; Judah will
        maintain its border from the south, and the house of Joseph will maintain
        its border from the north. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Describe the land in seven divisions, and bring it to me here; I
        will cast lots for you here before Yahweh our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Levites among you have no portion, for their inheritance is the
        priesthood of Yahweh; Gad, Reuben, and the half-tribe of Manasseh received
        their inheritance beyond the Jordan to the east, which Moses Yahweh\u2019s
        servant gave to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the men went immediately, and Joshua commanded the ones going
        to describe the land, saying, \u201CGo and walk about through the land, write
        a description, and return to me, and here I will cast a lot for you before
        Yahweh at Shiloh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the men went and passed through the land, and they described
        the cities in seven divisions in a book; and they came to Joshua to the camp
        at Shiloh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Allotment of Benjamin'
      title: The Allotment of Benjamin
      number: 10
      content: 'and Joshua cast a lot for them at Shiloh before Yahweh, and there
        he divided the land for the Israelites, to each a portion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the allotment of the tribe of Benjamin came up according to their
        families, and the border of their allotment fell between the descendants
        of Judah and the descendants of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Their northern border began at the Jordan and went up to the slope
        of Jericho on the north and continued into the hill country to the west;
        it ends at the wilderness of Beth Aven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The border passes on from there to Luz, to the slope of Luz to the
        south (that is, Bethel); then the border goes down to Ataroth Addar to the
        mountain that is south of Lower Beth-Horon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the border changes direction and turns to the western side southward,
        from the mountain that is opposite Beth-Horon to the south. It ends at Kiriath
        Baal (that is, Kiriath Jearim), a town belonging to the descendants of Judah.
        This is the western side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The southern side begins on the outskirts of Kiriath Jearim, and
        the border continues to the west to the spring of the waters of Nephtoah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the border goes down to the foot of the mountain, which is opposite
        the Valley of Ben Hinnom, which is in the valley of Rephaim to the north;
        then it does down the valley of Hinnom to the slope of the Jebusites to the
        south, and then it goes down to En Rogel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'It changes direction from the north, and it continues to En Shemesh;
        it goes out to Geliloth, which is opposite the ascent of Adummim, and it
        goes down to the stone of Bohan, son of Reuben. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'It passes on to the slope opposite the Arabah to the north, and it
        goes down to the Arabah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The border passes on to the slope of Beth-hoglah to the north and
        ends at the north bay of the Salt Sea at the south end of the Jordan. This
        is the southern border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The Jordan forms its border on the eastern side. This is the inheritance
        of the tribe of Benjamin, its borders that surrounds them, according to their
        families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the towns of the tribes of the descendants of Benjamin, according
        to their families, were Jericho, Beth-hoglah, Emek Keziz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Beth Arabah, Zemaraim, Bethel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Avvim, Parah, Ophrah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Kephar Ammoni, Ophni, and Geba; twelve cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Gibeon, Ramah, Beeroth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Mizpeh, Kephirah, Mozah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Rekem, Irpeel, Taralah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Zela, Haeleph, Jebus (that is, Jerusalem), Gibeah, and Kiriath; fourteen
        cities and their villages. This is the inheritance of the descendants of
        Benjamin according to their families. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Allotment of Simeon'
      title: The Allotment of Simeon
      number: 1
      content: 'The second allotment fell for Simeon, for the tribe of the descendants
        of Simeon, according to their families. And their inheritance was in the
        midst of the inheritance of the descendants of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And they had as their inheritance Beersheba, Sheba, Moladah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Hazar Shual, Balah, Ezem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Eltolad, Bethul, Hormah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ziklag, Beth Marcaboth, Hazar Susah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Beth Lebaoth, and Sharuhen; thirteen cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Ain, Rimmon, Ether, and Ashan; four cities and their villages, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and all the villages that were around these towns up to Baalat-Beor,
        Ramath of the Negev. This was the inheritance of the tribe of the descendants
        of Simeon according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Allotment of Zebulun'
      title: The Allotment of Zebulun
      number: 9
      content: 'Part of the portion allotted to the descendants of Judah became the
        inheritance of the descendants of Simeon because the portion for the descendants
        of Judah was too large for them, so the descendants of Simeon inherited from
        their inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The third allotment came up for the descendants of Zebulun according
        to their families. The border of their inheritance went up to Sarid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Their border goes up to the west, to Maralah; it touches Dabbesheth,
        then the wadi that is opposite Jokneam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'It turns from Sarid to the east to the sunrise, to the border of
        Kislot-Tabor; it continues to Daberath and goes up to Japhia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'From there it passes along to the east toward the sunrise, to Gath
        Hepher and to Eth Kazin, and continuing to Rimmon, it turns to Neah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'it changes direction from the north of Hannathon, and it ends at
        the valley of Yiptah-El; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Kattath, Nahalal, Shimron, Idalah, and Bethlehem; twelve cities and
        their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Allotment of Issachar'
      title: The Allotment of Issachar
      number: 16
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the descendants of Zebulun according to
        their families, these cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The fourth allotment fell for Issachar, for the descendants of Issachar,
        according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Their border went to Jezreel, Chesulloth, Shunem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hapharaim, Shion, Anaharath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Rabbith, Kishion, Ebez, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Remeth, En Gannim, En Haddah, and Beth Pazzez; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and the border touches Tabor, Shahazumah, and Beth Shemesh. Its border
        ends at the Jordan; sixteen cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The Allotment of Asher'
      title: The Allotment of Asher
      number: 23
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the tribe of the descendants of Issachar
        according to their families, the cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The fifth allotment fell for the tribe of the descendants of Asher
        according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Their border was Helkath, Hali, Beten, Acshaph, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Allamelech, Amad, and Mishal; it touches Carmel to the west, and
        Shihor-Libnat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then it turns eastward to Beth-dagon and touches Zebulun and the
        valley of Yiptah-El to the north to Beth Emeck and Neiel; it continues to
        Cabul from the north, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and Ebron, Rehob, Hammon, and Kanah up to Great Sidon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'then the border turns to Ramah, and up to the fortified city of Tyre,
        where the border turns to Hosah; it ends at the sea, from Hebel to Aczib. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Included were Ummah, Aphek, and Rehob; twenty-two cities and their
        villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: The Allotment of Naphtali'
      title: The Allotment of Naphtali
      number: 31
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the tribe of the descendants of Asher
        according to their families, these cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The sixth allotment fell for the children of Naphtali, for the children
        of Naphtali according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Their border was from Heleph, from the oak in Zaanannim, Adami Nekeb,
        Jabneel, up to Lakkum; it ends at the Jordan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'then the border turns to the west, to Aznoth Tabor, and continues
        from there to Hukok, and it touches Zebulun on the south, Asher on the west,
        and Judah on the east at the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The fortified cities are Ziddim, Zer, Hammath, Rakkath, Kinnereth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Adamah, Ramah, Hazor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Kedesh, Edrei, En Hazor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Yiron, Migdal El, Horem, Beth-anath, Beth Shemesh; nineteen cities
        and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: The Allotment of Dan'
      title: The Allotment of Dan
      number: 39
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Naphtali
        according to their families, the cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The seventh lot fell for the tribe of the descendants of Dan according
        to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The border of their inheritance was Zorah, Eshtaol, Ir Shemesh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Shaalabbin, Aijalon, Ithlah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Elon, Timnah, Ekron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Eltekeh, Gibbethon, Baalath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Jehud, Bene Berak, Gath Rimmon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Me Jarkon, Rakkon, with the border opposite Joppa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'The border of the descendants of Dan continued beyond them, because
        the descendants of Dan went up and fought with Lesham, and they captured
        and struck it with the edge of the sword, and they took possession of it
        and settled in it; and they called Leshem Dan, after the name of Dan their
        ancestor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: The Allotment Is Completed'
      title: The Allotment Is Completed
      number: 48
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the tribe of the descendants of Dan according
        to their families, these cities and their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'They finished assigning the land according to its borders, and the
        Israelites gave an inheritance from among them to Joshua son of Nun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'According to the commandment of Yahweh, they gave him the city that
        he requested, Timnath Serah, in the hill country of Ephraim, and he rebuilt
        the city and settled in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'These are the inheritances that Eleazar the priest, Joshua son of
        Nun, and the heads of the families of the tribes, distributed by allotment
        to the Israelites, at Shiloh before Yahweh at the entrance of the tent of
        meeting. And they finished dividing the land. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cities of Refuge Are Established'
      title: Cities of Refuge Are Established
      number: 1
      content: 'And Yahweh spoke to Joshua, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSpeak to the Israelites, saying, \u2018Appoint for yourselves
        cities of refuge, of which I spoke to you through the hand of Moses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Anyone who kills a person by accident or unintentionally may flee
        there; they will be for yourselves a refuge from the avenger of blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The killer will flee to one of these cities, stand at the entrance
        of the gate of the city, and state his case to the elders of that city; and
        they will take him into the city and give him a place, and he will dwell
        among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And if the avenger of blood pursues after him, they will not hand
        over the killer into his hand, because he killed his neighbor unintentionally,
        and he did not hate him previously.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The killer will stay in that city until he stands before the congregation
        for the trial, until the death of the one who is the high priest in those
        days. Then the killer will return to his city and to his house, to the city
        from which he fled.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So they set apart Kedesh in Galilee in the hill country of Naphtali,
        Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim, and Kiriath Arba (that is, Hebron)
        in the hill country of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Beyond the Jordan east of Jericho, they appointed Bezer in the wilderness
        on the plateau, from the tribe of Reuben, Ramoth in Gilead, from the tribe
        of Gad, and Golan in the Bashan, from the tribe of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'These were the cities designated for all the Israelites, and for
        the foreigners dwelling among them, for anyone that kills a person unintentionally
        to flee there, and not die by the hand of the avenger of blood, until there
        is a trial before the congregation. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Allotment of the Levites'
      title: The Allotment of the Levites
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the heads of the families of the Levites came to Eleazar the
        priest, to Joshua son of Nun, and to the heads of the families of the tribes
        of the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And they spoke to them at Shiloh in the land of Canaan, saying, \u201CYahweh
        commanded through the hand of Moses to give us cities to live in, with their
        pasturelands for our livestock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So, by command of Yahweh, the Israelites gave the Levites these cities
        and their pasturelands from their inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The allotment fell for the families of the Kohathites. The descendants
        of Aaron the priest, who were of the Levites, received by lot thirteen towns
        from the tribes of Judah, Simeon, and Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The remaining descendants of Kohath received by lot ten cities from
        the families of the tribes of Ephraim, Dan, and the half-tribe of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The descendants of Gershon received by lot thirteen cities from the
        families of the tribes of Issachar, Asher, and Naphtali and from the half-tribe
        of Manasseh in Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The descendants of the Merarites according to their families received
        twelve cities from the tribes of Reuben, Gad, and Zebulun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Israelites gave to the Levites these cities and their pastureland
        by lot, just as Yahweh commanded through the hand of Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They gave these cities, which are here mentioned by name, from the
        tribe of the families of Judah and from the tribe of the families of Simeon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and they were for the descendants of Aaron, from the families of
        the Kohathites, from the descendants of Levi, because the first lot was theirs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they gave to them Kiriath Arba, Arba being the father of Anak
        (that is, Hebron), in the hill country of Judah and the pasturelands surrounding
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the field of the city and its villages they gave to Caleb son
        of Jephunneh as his property. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'To the descendants of Aaron the priest they gave Hebron, the city
        of refuge for the killer, and its pasturelands, Libnah and its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Jattir and its pasturelands, Eshtemoa and its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Holon and its pasturelands, Debir and its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Ain and its pasturelands, Juttah and its pasturelands, and Beth Shemesh
        and its pasturelands; nine cities from these two tribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'From the tribe of Benjamin, Gibeon and its pasturelands, Geba and
        its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Anathoth and its pasturelands, Almon and its pasturelands; four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'All the cities of the descendants of Aaron the priests, thirteen
        cities and their pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the families of the descendants of Kohath, the remaining Levites
        of the descendants of Kohath, they received the cities of their lot from
        the tribe of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They gave them Shechem, the city of refuge for the killer, and its
        pasturelands in the hill country of Ephraim, Gezer and its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Kibzaim and its pasturelands, and Beth-horon and its pasturelands;
        four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'From the tribe of Dan, Eltekeh and its pasturelands, Gibbethon and
        its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Aijalon and its pasturelands, and Gath Rimmon and its pasturelands;
        four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'From the half-tribe of Manasseh, Taanach and its pasturelands and
        Gath Rimmon with its pasturelands; two cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'All the cities and their pasturelands for the remaining families
        of the descendants of Kohath were ten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'To the descendants of Gershon, one of the families of the Levites,
        from the half-tribe of Manasseh, Golan in Bashan, a city of refuge for the
        killer, and its pasturelands, and Eshtarah and its pasturelands; two cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'From the tribe of Issachar, Kishion and its pasturelands, Daberath
        and its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Jarmuth and its pasturelands, En Gannim and its pasturelands; four
        cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'From the tribe of Asher, Mishal and its pasturelands, Abdon and its
        pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Helkath and its pasturelands, Rehob and its pasturelands; four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'From the tribe of Naphtali, Kedesh in Galilee, the city of refuge
        for the killer, and its pasturelands, Hammoth Dor and its pasturelands, and
        Kartan and its pasturelands; three cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'All the cities of the Gershonites according to their families were
        thirteen cities and their pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'To the families of the descendants of Merarite, the remaining Levites,
        from the tribe of Zebulun, Jokneam and its pasturelands, Kartah and its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Dimnah and its pasturelands, and Nahalal and its pasturelands; four
        cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'From the tribe of Reuben, Bezer and its pasturelands, Jahaz and its
        pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Kedemoth and its pasturelands, and Mephaath and its pasturelands;
        four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'From the tribe of Gad, Ramoth in Gilead, the city of refuge for the
        killer, and its pasturelands, Mahanaim and its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Heshbon and its pasturelands, and Jazer and its pasturelands; four
        cities in all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'All these were the cities of the descendants of Merarite according
        to their families, the remaining families of the Levites; their allotment
        was twelve cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'All the cities of the Levites among the property of the Israelites
        were forty-eight cities and their pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Each of these cities had pasturelands surrounding them; so it was
        for all of these cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And Yahweh gave to Israel all the land that he swore to give to their
        ancestors, and they took possession of it and settled in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Yahweh gave them rest on every side, according to all that he had
        sworn to their ancestors, and nobody from all their enemies withstood them,
        for Yahweh had given all their enemies into their hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And nothing failed from all the good things that Yahweh promised
        to the house of Israel; everything came to pass.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Eastern Tribes Return'
      title: The Eastern Tribes Return
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Joshua summoned the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe
        of Manasseh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and he said to them, \u201CYou have observed all that Moses Yahweh\u2019s
        servant commanded you, and you have listened to my voice in all that I have
        commanded you; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'you have not forsaken your kinsmen these many days, up to this day,
        and you have observed the obligation of the command of Yahweh your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So then, Yahweh your God has given rest to your kinsmen, just as
        he promised them; so then, turn and go to your tents to the land of your
        possession, which Moses Yahweh\u2019s servant gave to you beyond the Jordan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Only be very careful to observe the commandment and law that Moses
        Yahweh\u2019s servant commanded you, to love Yahweh your God, to walk in
        all his ways, to keep his commandments, to hold fast to him, and to serve
        him with all your heart and with all your soul.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Joshua blessed them and sent them away, and they went to their
        tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And to the half-tribe of Manasseh Moses had given a possession in
        Bashan, but to the other half Joshua had given a possession with their kinsmen
        beyond the Jordan to the west; and when Joshua sent them to their tents and
        blessed them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "he said to them, \u201CReturn to your tents with much wealth, and
        with very much livestock, with silver, gold, copper, iron, and with very
        much clothing; divide the war-booty of your enemies with your kinsmen.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the descendants of Reuben, Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh
        returned home and departed with the Israelites at Shiloh, which is in the
        land of Canaan, to go to the land of Gilead to the land of their possession,
        which they had acquired according to the command of Yahweh through the hand
        of Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And they came to the region of the Jordan that is in the land of
        Canaan, and the descendants of Reuben, Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh
        built there an altar on the Jordan, a large and imposing altar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the Israelites heard it said that the descendants of Reuben,
        Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh had built an altar next to the land of
        Canaan, in the region of the Jordan, on the side belonging to the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When the Israelites heard of it, the whole congregation of the Israelites
        gathered at Shiloh to go up against them for battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the Israelites sent to the descendants of Reuben, Gad, and the
        half-tribe of Manasseh, to the land of Gilead, Phinehas the priest son of
        Eleazar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and ten leaders with him, one leader for each family from each of
        the tribes of Israel; and each one was the head of his family among the clans
        of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They came to the descendants of Reuben, Gad, and the half-tribe of
        Manasseh, to the land of Gilead, and they spoke with them, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThus says all the congregation of Yahweh: \u2018What is this
        treachery that you have committed against the God of Israel by turning away
        today from following Yahweh, by building for yourselves an altar to rebel
        today against Yahweh? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Is not the sin of Peor enough for us, from which we have not cleansed
        ourselves today, and for which a plague came to the congregation of Yahweh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'that you must turn today from following Yahweh? If you rebel today
        against Yahweh, tomorrow he will be angry with all of the congregation of
        Israel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "if, however, the land of your property is unclean, cross over to
        the land of Yahweh\u2019s property, where Yahweh\u2019s tabernacle resides,
        and take possession among us. But you must not rebel against Yahweh or against
        us by building for yourselves an altar other than the altar of Yahweh our
        God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Did not Achan son of Zerah commit treachery with devoted things,
        and wrath fell on all the congregation of Israel? And he alone did not perish
        because of his iniquity.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the descendants of Reuben, Gad, and the half-tribe of Manasseh
        spoke with the heads of the clans of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CYahweh, God of gods! Yahweh, God of gods knows. And let Israel
        itself know, if it was in rebellion or treachery against Yahweh, do not spare
        us this day "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'for building for ourselves an altar to turn away from Yahweh, or
        if it was to offer burnt offerings, grain offerings, or fellowship offerings
        on it, may Yahweh himself take vengeance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But in fact, we have done this because of anxiety, because of a reason,
        saying, \u2018In the future your children may say to our children, \u2018What
        is the relationship between you and Yahweh the God of Israel?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Yahweh has made the Jordan a border between us and you, the descendants
        of Reuben and Gad; you have no portion in Yahweh.\u2019 So your children
        may put an end to our children worshiping Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So we said, \u2018Let us build immediately for ourselves an altar,
        not for burnt offerings or for sacrifices;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "instead, it is a witness between us and you, and between our generations
        after us for performing the serving of Yahweh in his presence with our burnt
        offerings, sacrifices, and fellowship offerings; so that your children may
        not say in the future to our children, \u201CYou have no portion in Yahweh.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And we thought, if they say to us and to our children in the future,
        we can say, \u2018Look at this replica of the altar of Yahweh, which our
        ancestors made, not for burnt offerings or sacrifices; rather, it is a witness
        between us and you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Far be it from us to rebel against Yahweh, to turn today from following
        Yahweh, to build an altar for burnt offerings, grain offerings, or sacrifices,
        instead of the altar of Yahweh our God that is before his tabernacle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Phinehas the priest, the leaders of the congregation, and the heads
        of the clans of Israel who were with him heard the words that the descendants
        of Reuben, Gad, and Manasseh spoke, and they were satisfied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Phinehas the priest, son of Eleazar, said to the descendants of Reuben,
        Gad, and Manasseh, \u201CToday we know that Yahweh is among us, because you
        have not committed this treachery against Yahweh. Therefore you have rescued
        the Israelites from the hand of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And Phinehas the priest, son of Eleazar, and the leaders returned
        from the descendants of Reuben and Gad, from the land of Gilead, to the land
        of Canaan to the Israelites, and they gave them their report.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The report satisfied the Israelites; they blessed God, and they did
        not speak of going up for battle against them to destroy the land in which
        the descendants of Reuben and Gad were living.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "The descendants of Reuben and Gad called the altar Witness, \u201CBecause,\u201D
        they said, \u201Cit is a witness between us that Yahweh is God.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joshua\u2019s Farewell Address"
      title: "Joshua\u2019s Farewell Address"
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened, after a long time, after Yahweh had given rest to
        Israel from all their surrounding enemies, and after Joshua was old and well-advanced
        in years,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Joshua summoned all Israel, their elders, heads, judges, and officials,
        and he said to them, \u201CI am old and well-advanced in years,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and you have seen all that Yahweh your God has done to all these
        nations for your sake, for Yahweh your God is fighting for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Look! I have allotted to you these remaining nations as an inheritance
        for your tribes, from the Jordan, with all the nations that I have cut off,
        to the Great Sea in the west.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Yahweh your God will push them back before you and drive them
        out of your sight, and you will possess their land, just as Yahweh your God
        promised to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Be very strong to observe carefully all that is written in the scroll
        of the law of Moses so as not to turn aside from it, to the right or left, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'so as not to go among these remaining nations with you; do not profess
        the name of their gods, and do not swear by them, serve them, or bow down
        to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But hold fast to Yahweh your God, just as you have done up to this
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Yahweh has driven out before you great and strong nations; and as
        for you, nobody has withstood you to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'One of your men put to flight a thousand, for Yahweh your God is
        fighting for you, just as he promised you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Take utmost care for the sake of your life to love Yahweh your God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'for if indeed you turn back and join these remaining nations among
        you, and you intermarry with them, marrying their women and they yours,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'know for certain that Yahweh your God will not continue to drive
        out these nations from before you; they will be for you a snare and a trap,
        a whip on your sides and thorns in your eyes, until you perish from this
        good land that Yahweh your God has given to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Look! I am about to die, and you know in all your hearts and souls
        that not one thing failed from all the good things that Yahweh your God promised
        concerning you; everything has been fulfilled; not one thing failed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But just as all the good things came to you that Yahweh your God
        promised, so will Yahweh bring to you all the bad things until he has destroyed
        you from this good land that Yahweh your God has given to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "If you transgress the covenant of Yahweh your God, which he commanded
        to you, and you go and serve other gods and bow down to them, Yahweh\u2019s
        anger will be kindled against you, and you will perish quickly from the good
        land that he has given to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joshua Recounts Their History'
      title: Joshua Recounts Their History
      number: 1
      content: 'And Joshua gathered all the tribes of Israel to Shechem; he summoned
        the elders of Israel, their heads, their judges, and their officials, and
        they presented themselves before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Joshua said to all the people, \u201CThus says Yahweh the God
        of Israel: \u2018Long ago your ancestors\u2014Terah the father of Abraham
        and the father of Nahor\u2014lived beyond the river, and they served other
        gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I took your ancestor Abraham from beyond the river and led him through
        all the land of Canaan, and I increased his offspring; I gave him Isaac, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and to Isaac I gave Jacob and Esau. To Esau I gave the hill country
        of Seir to possess, but Jacob and his children went down to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I sent Moses and Aaron, and I plagued Egypt with what I did in
        its midst; and afterward I brought you out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When I brought out your ancestors from Egypt, you came to the sea,
        and the Egyptians pursued after your ancestors with chariots and horsemen
        to the Red Sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They cried out to Yahweh, and he put darkness between you and the
        Egyptians, and he brought the sea over them and covered them; your own eyes
        saw what I did in Egypt. Then you lived in the wilderness for many days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And I brought you to the land of the Amorites who lived beyond the
        Jordan; they fought you, and I gave them into your hand; you took possession
        of their land, and I destroyed them before you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Balak son of Zippor, king of Moab, set out and fought against
        Israel, and he sent and summoned Balaam son of Beor to curse you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but I was not willing to listen to Balaam, and he richly blessed
        you. So I rescued you from his hand, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and you crossed the Jordan and came to Jericho. And the citizens
        of Jericho, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Canaanites, the Hittites, the
        Girgashites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites, fought against you, and I gave
        them into your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I sent before you the hornet and they drove out before you two kings
        of the Amorites; but not by your sword or bow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Israelites Promise to Serve Yahweh'
      title: The Israelites Promise to Serve Yahweh
      number: 13
      content: "I gave to you a land that you have not labored on, and cities that
        you have not built, and you live in them; you eat from vineyards and olive
        groves that you have not planted.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CSo now, revere Yahweh and serve him in sincerity and faithfulness;
        remove the gods that your ancestors served beyond the river and in Egypt,
        and serve Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But if it is bad in your eyes to serve Yahweh, choose for yourselves
        today whom you want to serve, whether it is the gods that your ancestors
        served beyond the river, or the gods of the Amorites in whose land you are
        living; but as for me and my household, we will serve Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the people answered and said, \u201CFar be it from us that we
        would forsake Yahweh to serve other gods, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for Yahweh our God brought us and our ancestors from the land of
        Egypt, from the house of slavery, and did these great signs before our eyes.
        He protected us along the entire way that we went, and among all the peoples
        through whose midst we passed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Yahweh drove out all the people before us, the Amorites who live
        in the land. We will serve Yahweh, for he is our God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But Joshua said to the people, \u201CYou cannot serve Yahweh, for
        he is a holy and jealous God; he will not forgive your transgressions or
        your sins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "If you forsake Yahweh and serve foreign gods, he will turn and bring
        disaster to you; he will destroy you after he has done good to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the people said to Joshua, \u201CNo, we will serve Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Joshua said to the people, \u201CYou are witnesses against yourselves
        that you have chosen for yourselves to serve Yahweh.\u201D And they said,
        \u201CWe are witnesses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He said, \u201CRemove the foreign gods that are in your midst, and
        incline your hearts to Yahweh the God of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the people said to Joshua, \u201CWe will serve Yahweh our God,
        and we will listen to his voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So Joshua made a covenant with the people on that day, and he established
        for them a statute and a judgment at Shechem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then Joshua wrote these words in a scroll of the law of God, and
        he took a large stone and set it up there under a large tree, which is at
        the shrine of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Joshua said to all the people, \u201CLook, this stone will be
        a witness against us, for it has heard all the words of Yahweh that he spoke
        with us. It will be as a witness against you, so that you do not deny your
        God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then Joshua sent the people away to their inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'After these things Joshua son of Nun servant of Yahweh died; he was
        one hundred and ten years old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'They buried him in the territory of his inheritance, at Timnath-Serah,
        which is in the hill country of Ephraim, north of Mount Gaash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Israel served Yahweh all the days of Joshua, and all the days of
        the elders who lived long after Joshua, and who had known all the work that
        Yahweh did for Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The bones of Jacob, which the Israelites had brought out from Egypt,
        they buried at Shechem, in a piece of land that Jacob had bought from the
        children of Hamor, the father of Shechem, for one hundred pieces of money;
        it became an inheritance for the descendants of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And Eleazar son of Aaron died; and they buried him in Gibeah in the
        hill country of Ephraim, which had been given to his son Phinehas. '
      comments: []
